      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T19:33:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "mEmptyQueueCond is used to control the reading loop in VideoPlayer.cpp (av_read_frame), so we don\u0027t end up pushing too much frames into the packet queue, but if the queue is empty, then we signal it here.\n\nThe flush packet is put here pretty much for future use, in the case of seeking, so we can call avcodec_flush_buffers().\n\nThe serial number is actually related to flush too, which you can ignore. The condition is mainly controlled by mPacketPending and pkt.data !\u003d PacketQueue::sFlushPkt.data, only first packet will be pkt.data \u003d\u003d PacketQueue::sFlushPkt.data for now.",
      "parentUuid": "16ff47f1_303bd03d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 106,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "13d1c0cd0f9213cf3ba7fdf452f76ac31a4ef02d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a74e4486_318af537",
